-- Alvarion Declines to Record Low After Cutting Revenue Forecast
-- B y   S h o s h a n n a   S o l o m o n
-- 2012-04-05T13:51:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-05/alvarion-declines-to-record-low-after-cutting-revenue-forecast.html
Alvarion Ltd. (ALVR)  declined to the lowest
level on record after the telecommunications-equipment maker cut
its first-quarter revenue forecast and said it will be in
default of a financial covenant.  The  shares  dropped 18 percent to 2.848 shekels, the lowest
level since July 2001 when Bloomberg started tracking the data,
at the 4:30 p.m. close in  Tel Aviv .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Shoshanna Solomon in Tel Aviv at 
